Review comment:
       As stated in my PR comment, the `read_batch` function can receive any combination of `batch_size`, `def_levels.len()`, `rep_levels.len()` and `values.len()`. If the `batch_size` is the limiting factor your `iter_batch_size` might end up larger than the `batch_size`. This happened to me when called from `record_reader.rs` on a parquet file with relatively small row groups (500k rows). I did not manage to reproduce the phenomenon with a mock data file though ... :-/




